mistral.reason: The Gorlice-Tarnów Offensive occurred during World War I, and the 56th Infantry Division (56.  Infanterie-Division) was active only from 1915 to 1919, which falls within the timeframe of World War I but is after the Gorlice-Tarnów Offensive in May/June 1915. Therefore, it could not have been involved in this offensive.
